description: This file defines a data model for movie scripts using Pydantic, and sets up two Agent instances for generating movie scripts via OpenAI responses, one in JSON mode and one with structured outputs. It also includes example method calls to print responses for a given prompt.

classes.name: MovieScript
classes.description: A Pydantic model representing the structure of a movie script, including setting, ending, genre, name, characters, and storyline.

methods.name: print_response
methods.description: Method called on Agent instances to print the generated response for a given prompt.
